msgid "## 9 Performance Tuning"
msgstr ""

msgid "### 9.1 Recommended Configurations"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Scenario | Deployment Mode | Total NPUs | Weight Version | Key Considerations |\n"
"| -------- | --------------- | ---------- | -------------- | ------------------ |\n"
"| Long context | Single-node online serving | 16 A3 NPUs | W8A8 MTP | Use larger `--max-model-len` and reserve enough KV cache. Lower `--max-num-seqs` if OOM occurs. |\n"
"| High throughput | Multi-node MP | 16 A2 NPUs | W8A8 MTP | Increase concurrency through DP and tune `--max-num-batched-tokens` for prefill throughput. |\n"
"| Low latency | 1P1D PD disaggregation | 48 A3 NPUs | W8A8 MTP | Use separate prefill and decode DP/TP layouts and enable full decode ACLGraph on decode nodes. |"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Scenario | Node Role | NPUs | TP | DP | Max Num Seqs | Max Model Len | Max Num Batched Tokens | MTP Tokens | Prefix Cache | Main Optimizations |\n"
"| -------- | --------- | ---- | -- | -- | ------------ | ------------- | ---------------------- | ---------- | ------------ | ------------------ |\n"
"| Long context | Single node | 16 | 16 | 1 | 128 | 133000 | 16384 | 3 | On | FullGraph, FlashComm1, Fused MC2, CPU binding |\n"
"| High throughput | MP node | 8 per node | 8 | 1 per node, 2 global | 16 per DP | 32768 | 4096 | 3 | Off | FullGraph, shared expert overlap, CPU binding |\n"
"| Low latency | Prefill node | 16 | 2 | 8 | 64 | 16384 | 4096 | 3 | Off | Recompute scheduler, Fused MC2, CPU binding |\n"
"| Low latency | Decode node | 16 per node | 2 | 8 per node, 16 global | 32 | 16384 | 128 | 3 | Off | FullGraph, recompute scheduler, Fused MC2, CPU binding |"
msgstr ""

msgid "### 9.2 Tuning Guidelines"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"1. Set the deployment topology first. Use single-node deployment for validation, MP deployment for simple multi-node serving, and PD disaggregation when prefill and decode need different resource ratios.\n"
"2. Choose the maximum context length with `--max-model-len`. Long context increases KV cache usage, so reduce `--max-num-seqs` or `--gpu-memory-utilization` if OOM occurs.\n"
"3. Tune `--max-num-batched-tokens`. Larger values usually improve prefill throughput but increase activation memory. Decode-heavy workloads usually need smaller values.\n"
"4. Tune `--max-num-seqs` according to service concurrency. Requests above this value wait in the queue and the waiting time is counted in TTFT and TPOT.\n"
"5. Tune `--gpu-memory-utilization`. Increase it to provide more KV cache, but leave headroom for runtime memory fluctuation and expert imbalance.\n"
"6. Tune `--speculative-config`. MTP can improve decode throughput, but the best `num_speculative_tokens` depends on acceptance rate and workload.\n"
"7. Tune ACLGraph capture. `FULL_DECODE_ONLY` is recommended for decode. If you set `cudagraph_capture_sizes` manually, include common decode batch sizes. With FlashComm1, use capture sizes that are multiples of TP size."
msgstr ""

msgid "### 9.3 Model-Specific Optimizations"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Optimization | Enablement | Benefit | Notes |\n"
"| ------------ | ---------- | ------- | ----- |\n"
"| Rope optimization | Enabled by default | Reuses position encoding work across layers to reduce decode overhead. | No extra configuration is required. |\n"
"| AddRMSNormQuant fusion | Enabled by default | Fuses normalization and quantization to reduce memory access. | Applies to quantized paths. |\n"
"| Zero-like elimination | Enabled by default | Removes unnecessary zero-like tensor operations in attention. | No extra configuration is required. |\n"
"| Qwen3.5 MTP speculative decoding | `--speculative-config '{\"method\": \"qwen3_5_mtp\", \"num_speculative_tokens\": 3, \"enforce_eager\": true}'` | Improves decode throughput when acceptance rate is good. | Reduce speculative tokens if latency or stability regresses. |\n"
"| Full decode ACLGraph | `--compilation-config '{\"cudagraph_mode\":\"FULL_DECODE_ONLY\"}'` | Reduces operator dispatch overhead and stabilizes decode performance. | Recommended for decode-heavy serving. |\n"
"| FlashComm1 | `--additional-config '{\"enable_flashcomm1\": true}'` | Reduces communication overhead in large TP and high-concurrency scenarios. | May not help low-concurrency workloads. |\n"
"| Fused MC2 | `--additional-config '{\"enable_fused_mc2\": 1}'` | Enables MoE fused operators to improve MoE prefill/decode efficiency. | If accuracy or performance regresses in multi-DP large-token scenarios, disable it and compare. |\n"
"| Shared expert overlap | `--additional-config '{\"multistream_overlap_shared_expert\": true}'` | Overlaps shared expert computation in MoE workloads. | Recommended for MP throughput scenarios. |\n"
"| Recompute scheduler | `--additional-config '{\"recompute_scheduler_enable\": true}'` | Recomputes KV through prefill when decode KV cache is insufficient in PD mode. | Only valid on decode nodes where `kv_role` is `kv_consumer`. |\n"
"| CPU binding | `--additional-config '{\"enable_cpu_binding\": true}'` | Improves CPU affinity and reduces scheduling jitter on ARM servers. | Enabled by default in many configurations, but explicitly setting it keeps the recipe clear. |"
msgstr ""

